Durban - A 43-year-old suspect was arrested following the death of a 40-year-old jogger in Hillcrest, Durban, this past Saturday. According to KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala, the suspect was arrested for failing to report an accident and is due to appear in the Pinetown Magistrate's Court next week. "The body of 40-year-old man was side of the road with injuries after being hit by a vehicle. A case of culpable homicide is being investigated by Hillcrest SAPS," said Gwala. According to Russel Meiring, spokesperson for ER24, the man's body was found on the side of the road in Winston Park, between Gillitts and Hillcrest, KwaZulu-Natal. "Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained a significant head injury and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead." By Sunday afternoon the jogger had not been identified. POST